","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Some of the strongest attitudes towards mental health are evident in three questions that were asked","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Do you believe your productivity is ever affected by a mental health issue?","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"ordered"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Do you feel that being identified as a person with a mental health issue would hurt your career?","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"ordered"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"Would you bring up a mental health issue with a potential employer in an interview?","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"ordered"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"94% of the respondents to the question believe that their productivity is affected by a mental health issue","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"46% of the respondents believe that being identified as a person with a mental health issue would hurt their career while 12% believed it wouldn't","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"61% of respondents would not bring up the fact they had a mental health issue with a potential employer","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":"All these attitudes would lead one to think employee's feel that mental health affects their performance in work but would be worried about how it would affect their career or worried about what a potential employer thinks of their condition.","textStyle":{"fontSize":"11pt"}}],"listType":"bullet"},{"textRuns":[{"value":""}]},{"textRuns":[{"value":"The findings of whether the size of an organisation has an impact on mental health all pointed to the same conclusion -
